## ChatCopsServerConfig

```typescript
interface ChatCopsServerConfig {
  provider: {
    type: 'claude' | 'openai' | 'gemini';
    apiKey: string;
    model?: string;
  };
  systemPrompt: string;
  tools?: ChatTool[];
  knowledge?: KnowledgeSource[];
  rateLimit?: {
    maxRequests: number;
    windowMs: number;
  };
  webhooks?: WebhookConfig[];
  analytics?: boolean;
  cors?: string;
  i18n?: {
    defaultLocale: string;
    locales: Record<string, LocaleStrings>;
  };
}
```

## Request Schema

The server validates incoming requests with Zod:

```typescript
{
  conversationId: string,  // 1-128 chars
  message: string,         // 1-10000 chars
  pageContext?: {           // Optional page context
    url: string,           // Valid URL
    title: string,         // Max 500 chars
    description?: string,  // Max 1000 chars
    contentSnippet?: string, // Max 2000 chars
  },
  locale?: string,         // Max 10 chars
}
```

## Response Format

The server responds with SSE (Server-Sent Events) for streaming:

```
Content-Type: text/event-stream

data: {"type":"token","content":"Hello"}
data: {"type":"token","content":" there"}
data: {"type":"token","content":"!"}
data: {"type":"done"}
```

The `ChatCops` singleton is exposed on `window.ChatCops` when using the IIFE bundle, or importable from the ESM bundle.

## Methods

### `ChatCops.init(config)`

Initialize the widget with a configuration object. Must be called before any other method if not using script tag auto-init.

```typescript
ChatCops.init({
  apiUrl: 'https://your-api.com/chat',
  theme: { accent: '#6366f1' },
  branding: { name: 'My Bot' },
  welcomeMessage: 'Hello! How can I help?',
});
```

### `ChatCops.open()`

Programmatically open the chat panel.

```typescript
document.querySelector('#help-btn').addEventListener('click', () => {
  ChatCops.open();
});
```

### `ChatCops.close()`

Close the chat panel.

```typescript
ChatCops.close();
```

### `ChatCops.destroy()`

Completely remove the widget from the DOM and clean up all event listeners.

```typescript
ChatCops.destroy();
```

### `ChatCops.on(event, callback)`

Subscribe to widget events. Returns an unsubscribe function.

```typescript
const unsub = ChatCops.on('message', (data) => {
  console.log('New message:', data);
});

// Later: unsubscribe
unsub();
```

### `ChatCops.off(event, callback)`

Remove a specific event listener.

```typescript
function onOpen() {
  console.log('Widget opened');
}

ChatCops.on('open', onOpen);
ChatCops.off('open', onOpen);
```

## Auto-Initialization

When using the CDN script tag, the widget auto-initializes by reading `data-*` attributes:

```html
<script
  src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@chatcops/widget/dist/chatcops.min.js"
  data-api-url="https://your-api.com/chat"
  data-accent="#6366f1"
></script>
```

The script tag approach is equivalent to calling `ChatCops.init()` with the corresponding config. You can still use the programmatic API after auto-init (e.g., `ChatCops.open()`).

